I have just one simple prediction for Drupal in 2008;
Drupal becomes to websites and the website-producing industry, what Linux is to webservers and the web-hosting industry.
Realistically this will probably take well into 2009 for this to be effective to the extent that linux, but the foundations for this are already laid and I believe that with the current momentum, it's just time before my prediction becomes true.

A graph from the article showing disabilities reported: Read the full article I recently read a fascinating survey of 1000 blind and visually impaired internet users. It's a long article but is largely graphs and data tables – so is easily consumed. If you want the short version, check out the comments and conclusion.
The most surprising parts for me were;
Websites that auto-play music (MySpace most notably) are extremely difficult because the sound makes it hard for the user to listen to screen readers.

